  {
    "id": "f_csv_d82e8afcb8",
    "slug": "sometimes-trust-is-something-born-only-out-of-necessity-a-curtain-we-draw-to-h",
    "texto": "Sometimes, trust is something born only out of necessity. A curtain we draw to hide the ugly truth in order to convince ourselves that everything is fine, when deep down, we know nothing is fine. Crazy logic, I know. But take it from someone who knows. I trust people just enough to keep my head above water, but never completely. No matter how much you invest in a person, no matter how much think you can trust them, you can always be fooled.",
